  "duration": 108.251430912,
  "text": " Is your organizational structure designed for effectiveness and efficiency? Adaptable organizations are built on purpose and meaning, organized for effectiveness and efficiency, optimized for the future workforce, and designed for human-centered realities. In uncertain times, organizations need to adapt quickly to change. The complexity of traditional enterprise structures often get in the way of meaningful work. Gig work, virtual work, and distributed workforces create even more complexity in how organizations and leaders need to manage teams. A new way of teaming may be totally incompatible with operations and culture. Adaptable organizations work to reduce these complexities in a sustainable way, so people on the front lines can make decisions quickly. Start by simplifying your organizational structure to eliminate bottlenecks, bloat, and bureaucracy. Use data-driven network models to understand how people work together across teams to improve collaboration. Then use these insights to identify and address the problems impacting business outcomes and employee career aspirations. And a bonus, reduce complexity equals reduce costs as well as improved employee and customer experiences. give your teams the space to focus on efforts that create real value. An adaptable organization uncovers efficiencies, finds hidden opportunities, and empowers network-based teams to adapt to change.",
